<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   DLK Leader Comments on `Grave' Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DLK Leader Comments on `Grave' Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2605201694 Tirana ATA in English 1033 GMT 26 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2605201694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, May 26 (ATA) -- The chairwoman of the 
Human Rights Fund, with its seat in Belgrade, Natasha Kandic, 
was received in Prishtina by the members of the presidency of 
DLK [Kosova Democratic Alliance], Chairman Dr. Fehmi Agani, 
deputy chairman, Edita Tahiri, and other members, who spoke 
about the grave situation in Kosova, as a result of Serb state 
organized oppression. The presidency of DLK presented to her 
the attitude, already known for the solution of Kosova issue, by 
peaceful means and through a referendum. 
  The chairman of the fund said that the organization is 
closely following the developments in Kosova, and added that she 
is compiling a special report for the situation in Kosova. She 
expressed her respect for the Albanians, who with their peaceful 
policy, are trying to solve Kosova issue. In the face of the 
continuous repression, Albanian people showed maturity and did 
not react to the provocations conducted by the Serb's regime, 
avoiding so the war. 

</TEXT>

