<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rector Cited on Closing of Pristina University </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rector Cited on Closing of Pristina University </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2505170794 Tirana ATA in English 0822 GMT 25 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2505170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, May 24 (ATA) -- In an interview with 
Behlul Jashari, ATA correspondent, on May 23, the rector of the 
Prishtina University, Prof. Dr. Ejup Statovci, said that the 
closing of the University of Prishtina by the Serbian 
authorities aims at preventing studies in the Albanian language. 
To this end, Serbian authorities have occupied the university 
premises through force, by not allowing over 900 teachers and 
over 20 thousand Albanian students to attend studies there. 
  According to Mr. Statovci, Albanian teachers and students 
have not interrupted teaching. The classes are being held, for 
the third consecutive year, in private homes in very difficult 
conditions. Almost the whole Prishtina is turned into a 
university. Despite the conditions, work goes on for the 
modernization of the teaching process. A law has also been 
prepared for the university based on the experience of the 
universities of Western countries. 
  Mr. Statovci said that they have good relations with the 
universities in Albania, particularly with the Tirana 
University, which has given them a great assistance. According 
to Mr. Statovci, these relations are not developing as they 
should for objective reasons, one of which is the impossible 
free movement of the people. 

</TEXT>

