<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Director on New Banking Duties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Director on New Banking Duties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2804164994 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>
<F P=103> PY2804164994 </F>
<F P=104>  -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in 
Portuguese 26 Apr 94 p 1 reports that Central Bank Norms 
Director Claudio Mauch has announced that as of 25 April the 
banks are authorized to issue Bank Deposit Certificates, CDB's, 
and Bank Deposit Receipts, RDB's, in Real Value Units, URV's. 
These certificates will thus earn a lower annual interest rate 
plus monetary correction which will be determined at the 
maturity date. This means investors will know their profits on 
the maturity date of the document. Savings accounts will 
continue to earn the Referential Interest Rate, TR, plus a 
6-percent annual interest. If the banks en mass adopt the URV, 
the Central Bank will have to modify the TR calculation formula. 
The TR is currently calculated on the interests paid by the 
prefixed CDB which is a preestablished interest-earning paper 
that does not receive monetary correction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

