<H3> <TI>   Military Reports: Lula May Win Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Reports: Lula May Win Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2804222294 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
28 Apr 94 p 6 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2804222294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "JB Report" column] </F>
  [Text] Electoral polls carried out by the Army Intelligence 
Center (CIE) and the Navy Intelligence Center (Cenimar) have 
both discovered that Lula [Luis Inacio da Silva, Worker's Party 
candidate] could win the elections for president in the first 
round. 
  The military analysts concluded that if a second round of 
voting were held in the elections, Lula's probable adversary 
would be former Governor Orestes Quercia from the PMDB 
[Brazilian Democratic Movement Party], and not Fernando Henrique 
Cardoso. According to the military analysts, Cardoso has a 
chance to win in the first round only in the state of Minas 
Gerais, where he has the support of Governor Helio Garcia. 
  The report was delivered to President Itamar Franco by a 
military minister. 

</TEXT>

