<F P=101> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cardoso Asks Magalhaes To Be Running Mate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cardoso Asks Magalhaes To Be Running Mate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2804221094 Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 
28 Apr 94 p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2804221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia -- Yesterday, Brazilian Social Democracy 
Party candidate Fernando Henrique Cardoso officially asked 
Deputy Luis Eduardo Magalhaes, PFL [Liberal Front Party] leader 
in the Chamber of Deputies, to join his ticket as candidate for 
vice president. Cardoso told Luis Eduardo that he would be vice 
presidential candidate in these elections only if he so desires, 
thus leaving the decision entirely in the hands of Luis Eduardo, 
who did not give a definite answer. 
  Although he did not clearly reject the invitation, Luis 
Eduardo expressed his reticence to Cardoso. The two talked for 
an hour and a half, analyzed an alliance between the two parties 
in the states, and settled the last details of an alliance that 
will be officially announced on 2 May. 
  Former Bahia Governor Antonio Carlos Magalhaes, father of 
Luis Eduardo, will meet with Cardoso in Rio de Janeiro tomorrow, 
but will not attend the ceremony on 2 May. Luis Eduardo 
admitted he has spoken with Cardoso about the vice presidency 
for the first time, but he did not want to give any details. 
"It would not be polite," he said. 
  Luis Eduardo said the PFL decision will probably be 
announced 
next weekend, depending on the date chosen for the party 
convention. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

