<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Premier Signs Cultural Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Premier Signs Cultural Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2204202494 Prague CTK in English 1910 GMT 22 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2204202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santiago de Chile April 22 (CTK) -- At the end of 
his three-day visit to Chile, Premier Vaclav Klaus signed a 
Czech-Chilean cultural agreement today. On behalf of Chile, the 
agreement was signed by Deputy Foreign Minister Jose Miguel 
Insulza. 
  The agreement provides for development of relations in 
culture, education and science, cooperation of media and 
exchanges of youth and sportsmen. It also envisages mutual 
presentation of works of art, exchange of books, dissemination 
of literature, direct cooperation of universities and scientific 
institutes and exchange trips of scholars and students. 
  In the afternoon, Klaus met leading parliamentary 
representatives. Late in the afternoon he is leaving for to 
Brazil, the last stop on his ten-day trip to South America. 

</TEXT>

