production and poultry breeding," the minister of the South 
American country told the media. 
  Ocampo's visit to Havana is part of a series of contacts 
made 
by Colombian ministers and personalities with local authorities, 
in an attempt to develop and improve bilateral commercial, 
cultural, and diplomatic relations. 
  Recently, the Colombian health minister visited the island 
and last year President Fidel Castro accepted an official 
invitation from his South American colleague Cesar Gaviria. 

