  [Text] The spokesman for President Aristide, Jean-Claude 
Martineau, has reacted to the antidrug operation led by the 
Haitian military authorities. The initiative has come too late, 
according to the president's spokesman. Martineau reaffirmed 
that the Haitian military authorities are involved up to the 
hilt in drug trafficking. 
  [Begin Martineau recording, in Creole] A big drug dealer 
made 
a series of statements before the U.S. Senate, perhaps one week 
