Colonel] Michel Francois [Port-au-Prince police chief] is 
involved up to the hilt in drug trafficking. Obviously, it was 
not necessary for anyone to come tell us about that to know it. 
Besides, this is something that President Aristide has been 
denouncing for some times. We have heard that there is an 
operation aimed at arresting drug dealers in Haiti. Why are they 
trying to arrest those involved in drug trafficking (?only) 
after this accusation, when they knew about it previously? [end 
recording] 
  This was the spokesman for President Aristide, Jean-Claude 
Martineau. 

