<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Opens Pilot Nuclear Fuel Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Opens Pilot Nuclear Fuel Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3004013494 Paris AFP in Spanish 2305 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA3004013494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 28 Apr (AFP) -- The Energy, Mines, and 
Parastate Industry minister has reported that the Mexican 
Government today opened a pilot plant to manufacture nuclear 
fuel to be used by the Laguna Verde Nuclear Plant, which is 
located on the coast of the Gulf of Mexico. The pilot plant, 
situated in the State of Mexico near Mexico City, was built at a 
cost of about $10 million, and, according to the minister, it 
was constructed "in line with the strictest security and quality 
standards." The minister added: Experts of the International 
Atomic Energy Agency will train the technicians who will operate 
the plant. 

</TEXT>

