<H3> <TI>   Lazo Greets Zambian President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lazo Greets Zambian President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2904180394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2904180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 29 April, Zambian President Frederick Chiluba and 
the high-level delegation accompanying him traveled to Santiago 
de Cuba Province where they are scheduled to meet with Zambian 
students in schools in Santiago de Cuba, Camaguey, and Moa, 
among other activities. 
  This morning, President Chiluba rendered homage to Jose 
Marti 
at Santa Efigenia Cemetery following his arrival at Antonio 
Maceo International Airport where he was greeted by Esteban Lazo 
Hernandez, member of the Politburo and first secretary of the 
Communist Party of Cuba in the province. 
  President Chiluba, accompanied by Foreign Minister Roberto 
Robaina, also visited the Antonio Maceo Revolution Square where 
he took in aspects of Maceo's thoughts and actions against 
Spanish colonialism. Chiluba and his delegation are now visiting 
the African Cultural Center and will visit, this afternoon, the 
Granjita Siboney Museum and the former Moncada Barracks, as well 
as meet with Zambian students in Santiago de Cuba. 

</TEXT>

