<H3> <TI>   Legislative Assembly Opens Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Legislative Assembly Opens Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0105184694 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1706 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0105184694 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador, 1 May (ACAN-EFE) -- El Salvador's 
Legislative Assembly, elected last 20 March and in which the 
former guerrillas are represented as the second largest 
political force, opened its session with a solemn ceremony today. 
  The first point on the agenda was the appointment of the 
Debate Commission--which later presided over the first plenary 
session--headed by Deputy Walter Rene Araujo, of the 
progovernment Nationalist Republican Alliance (ARENA, rightist). 
  Former guerrilla Commander Ana Guadalupe Martinez, of the 
Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front (FMLN), and labor 
leader Rosa Melida Villatoro, a deputy of the Christian 
Democratic Party (PDC), were appointed commission secretaries. 
  Ana Guadalupe Martinez, who with 20 other FMLN 
representatives form the second largest legislative force, read 
the roster of 84 deputies who make up the parliament. 
  Following this ceremony, Walter Araujo announced a one-hour 
recess so that the Debate Commission can receive the credentials 
of deputies and vote later to elect the board of directors. 

</TEXT>

