<H3> <TI>   Assembly President Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly President Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0205021294 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1828 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0205021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador, 1 May (ACAN-EFE) -- Gloria Salguero 
Gross, a deputy for the ruling Nationalist Republican Alliance 
(ultra right-wing ARENA) was elected by a split vote the new 
president of El Salvador's Legislative Assembly today, Sunday. 
  Salguero received the support of 70 of the 84 deputies that 
make up the assembly, including seven members of the former 
guerrilla Farabundo Marti National Liberation Movement (FMLN). 
The remaining 14 FMLN deputies abstained. 
  The presidential election took place during installation of 
the Legislative Assembly ceremonies. The process was marked by 
chants, jeers, and shouting by FMLN militants, who were 
protesting because the previous legislature changed the 
institution's bylaws, allowing the new president to vote twice. 

</TEXT>

