<H3> <TI>   Workers Threaten More Privatization Protests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Workers Threaten More Privatization Protests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2904214994 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 28 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2904214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The Voz Andes Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Edgard Ponce, president of the United Workers Front 
(FUT), said the government must change its policy or the 
demonstrations and protest strikes will continue to grow. 
Workers and peasants are unwilling to allow privatization of 
the Ecuadorean Social Security Institute, the state-owned 
telecommunications company, and the Ecuadorean Institute of 
Electrification. The FUT reiterated that the workers will take 
even more radical action if the government persists in its 
maniacal fervor to privatize state-run companies. 
  The FUT president added that joint action by the FUT, the 
public sector, the Confederation of Indian Nationalities of 
Ecuador, teachers, craftsmen, small merchants, and other sectors 
would have serious repercussions that the government can only 
prevent if it stops hijacking profitable state-run companies to 
give them away to private businessmen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

