<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Decrees `State of Internal Disturbance' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Decrees `State of Internal Disturbance' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0205000494 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2322 GMT 1 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0205000494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 1 May (DPA) -- The private 
Caracol radio station reported the Colombian Government decreed 
a state of internal disturbance tonight, thereby preventing the 
release of more than 700 inmates, including dangerous 
terrorists, drug traffickers, and guerrillas. This mechanism 
authorizes President Cesar Gaviria to issue special, temporary 
laws without the approval of the National Congress. 
  This is the only mechanism available to the Gaviria 
administration to prevent the mass release of inmates upon the 
completion of their prison terms because public prosecutors have 
failed to study their cases to begin their trials. 
  The decrees issued by Gaviria during this period will be 
valid for as long as the state of exception is in effect. 
According to the Constitution, the state of internal 
disturbance could last 90 days and could be extended for an 
additional 90 days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-56287 </DOCNO>
