  [Text] The Movement of Young Patriots [MOJEP] demands a 
total embargo to resolve the current crisis. The secretariat of 
MOJEP, as a political organization involved in the struggle of 
the Haitian people for the return of democracy, peace, and 
social security in the interest of all Haitians, is pleased to 
send this letter to Haiti's four friendly countries, the United 
States, France, Canada, and Venezuela, to solicit a total and 
impartial blockade to force the criminals of Port-au-Prince to 
hand over power to constitutional Haitian President 
Jean-Bertrand Aristide. They have monopolized it since the 
bloody military coup of 29 September 1991. 
  Dear countries friendly to Haiti, says MOJEP, we pray you to 
please show understanding by granting us this request. We count 
on your spirit of collaboration, says the letter signed by [word 
indistinct] Herve, organization secretary general, and Louis 
Bauduy Francois. 

