<H3> <TI>   Parties Agree To Hold Presidential Debate 12 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parties Agree To Hold Presidential Debate 12 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0305023294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0305023294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Luis Sarmenta] </F>
  [Text] Next Thursday, 12 May, a debate will take place 
between presidential candidates Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, Ernesto 
Zedillo, and Diego Fernandez de Cevallos. The PRI 
[Institutional Revolutionary Party], PAN [National Action 
Party], and PRD [Party of the Democratic Revolution] 
representatives who agreed to hold the debate on 12 May also 
decided that it would take place at 2100 to allow most of the 
Mexican people to watch the debate, which will be broadcast live. 
  At a brief news conference called by PRI Deputy Secretary 
General Esteban Moctezuma, PRD representative Adolfo Aguilar 
Zinzer, and PRI presidential candidate Diego Fernandez de 
Cevallos, it was announced that the site of the debate has not 
yet been determined. According to presidential candidate 
Fernandez de Cevallos, the site has not yet been selected 
because of technicalities and logistics that need to be worked 
out among the three parties. 
  [Begin recording] [Fernandez Cevallos, in progress] ...that 
the debate will take place on 12 May at 2100. It will only be 
possible to reschedule the debate through an agreement among the 
three of us. This is all of the information we have for you at 
this time. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Where will the debate be held, sir? 
  [Fernandez Cevallos] The site has not yet been determined. 
The selection of an appropriate site will depend on logistics. 
[end recording] 
  PRI representative Esteban Moctezuma noted that, so far, 
more 
than 10 possible debate sites are being studied. At any rate, 
it was explained that the exact site would be announced within 
the next few days. 

</TEXT>

