<F P=100> CENTRAL AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calderon Vows To Investigate Corruption Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calderon Vows To Investigate Corruption Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0205183294 San Salvador Canal Doce Television in Spanish 
0300 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0205183294 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Canal Doce Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Up-to-Date" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President-elect Dr. Armando Calderon Sol has pledged 
to fully investigate all complaints of corruption against any of 
his cabinet ministers. During an interview for the "Up-to-Date" 
newscast, the ARENA [Nationalist Republican Alliance] leader 
expressed his resolve to place in court custody all individuals 
found guilty of corruption. 
  Dr. Calderon Sol has only one goal regarding this issue: to 
combat institutionalized corruption regardless of its cost to 
the government. According to the president-elect, he cannot 
betray the people who supported him during the past elections. 
Therefore, he says, he will get to the bottom of all complaints 
of corruption. 
  [Begin Calderon Sol recording] If there are even rumors 
against any official, we will conduct a full investigation and 
place that person in court custody for investigation. [end 
recording] 
  Corruption, says the future president, will be fought at all 
levels, but especially in those areas involving goods, services, 
and public bids. Calderon Sol also intends to put an end to 
government official's involvement in organized crime. 
  [Begin Calderon Sol recording] If any administration 
officials are thus involved, regardless of who they may be, we 
will apply the law and break this circle of organized crime. 
[end recording] 
  Calderon Sol, who will take office in June, warned that 
during his term he will manage public funds carefully and 
strengthen the development of the National Civilian Police, 
which emerged from the peace agreements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

