<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Man Identified as Maritime Service Policeman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Man Identified as Maritime Service Policeman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0305034794 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 0238 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0305034794 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Panama City, 2 May (ACAN-EFE) -- The Democratic 
Revolutionary Party [PRD] reported today, Monday, that a 
policeman tried to shoot presidential candidate Ernesto Perez 
Balladares with a pistol. The man, who is in custody, said he 
drew the gun to fend off an assault. 
  The PRD, an opposition party, issued a communique describing 
the incident as "a foiled attempt" on Perez Balladares, whom 
opinion polls show as the favorite in next Sunday's general 
elections. 
  Electoral Tribunal Magistrate Dennis Allen, however, said 
the 
policeman, whom the PRD identified as Maritime Service Corporal 
Juan Bautista Zapata, said after being detained that he was just 
trying to repel an attacker who assaulted him while he was 
attending the PRD rally in downtown Panama City. Bautista 
Zapata was wearing civilian clothes at the time of the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

