<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Enforcement Accord With Jamaica Promulgated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drug Enforcement Accord With Jamaica Promulgated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0305012294 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 26 Apr 94 p C5 </F>
<F P=103> PY0305012294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Through the publication of a decree in the official 
gazette yesterday, the Foreign Ministry promulgated an agreement 
with Jamaica for the prevention, control, surveillance, and 
repression of the illegal consumption and trafficking of drugs 
and narcotics. 
  The agreement is signed by former President Patricio Aylwin. 
It was approved by Congress as stated in Resolution No. 1280 of 
the Chamber of Deputies. 
  The two governments are aware of the problems stemming from 
drugs, including the deterioration of economies and the harm to 
peoples' health. 
  The idea is to establish a permanent mechanism that will 
allow Chilean and Jamaican authorities to exchange information 
related to drug trafficking. 

</TEXT>

