<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Franco Modifies Measure on Real Value Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Franco Modifies Measure on Real Value Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0205140494 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 29 Apr 94 
p 25 </F>

<F P=103> PY0205140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Brasilia -- President Itamar Franco on 28 April 
signed a new version of the provisional measure that creates the 
Real Value Unit [URV] and the real. He introduced it with two 
modifications that had been negotiated with Congress: First, 
the guarantee of covering, beginning 1 July, any possible loss 
in purchasing power of salaries converted into URV's. This will 
be done if there is really any loss compared to the previous 
salary policy. Second, to ensure that the rules for issuance of 
the real comply with all legal demands and that the real will be 
implemented through a presidential decree. Provisional Measure 
No. 482, which was published in the official gazette today, does 
not establish a date for the new currency's implementation. 
Congress will have one month to vote on this provisional measure. 
  Although the economic team defended the idea of reissuing 
Provisional Measure No. 457 without modifying it, the opinion of 
the government's political area prevailed. In the afternoon of 
28 April, Finance Ministry executive secretary Clovis Carvalho 
stated: "Everyone believed the original text should be 
preserved." He pointed out, however, that it was up to Finance 
Minister Rubens Ricupero and the president of the Republic to 
make the final decision on the issue. Ricupero's chief of staff, 
Sergio Amaral, said the finance minister offered President 
Itamar Franco the two alternatives. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

