  [Text] In a meeting of the extended secretariat of the 
Cuban Workers Federation [CTC], chaired by CTC Secretary General 
Pedro Ross Leal, it was announced that the Assemblies for 
Economic Efficiency will be held in all work collectives 
beginning on 15 May. 
  A recent survey conducted to obtain reaction on the first 
assemblies of this type indicated that the assemblies constitute 
an important form of participation so that the collectives can 
measure their progress in production and services. 
  During the meeting, Ross insisted on the CTC's role in 
supporting the changes and transformations that are necessary 
and said that the Assemblies for Economic Efficiency preserve 
the spirit of the parliaments in the workplace. 

