<H3> <TI>   Alfonsin Elected UCR Bloc Leader </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alfonsin Elected UCR Bloc Leader </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY0205132294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1941 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0205132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 29 Apr (NA) -- UCR [Radical Civic 
Union] President Raul Alfonsin was elected on 29 April as 
president of the UCR bloc in the Constituent Assembly and 
Cordoba UCR leader Ramon Mestre was appointed first vice 
presidential candidate for the Constituent Assembly that will 
meet in the cities of Santa Fe and Parana. 
  Both decisions were made during the first 10 minutes of a 
meeting the UCR Constituent Assembly members are holding at the 
party's National Committee headquarters in Buenos Aires' 
Congreso neighborhood. 
  The motion for Alfonsin to preside over the UCR bloc was 
made 
by Antonio Hernandez, a pro-[Cordoba Governor Eduardo] Angeloz 
Constituent Assembly member from Cordoba, while Cesar 
Jaroslavsky, a pro-Alfonsin member from Buenos Aires, moved that 
Mestre be nominated first vice president of the Constituent 
Assembly. 

</TEXT>

